### Rules for Frontend

- You must pay attention to visual clarity and contrast. Do not place white text on a white background.
- You must ensure the UX is pleasant. Boxes should grow to fit their contents, etc. 
- When asking the user for sensitive information - you must use password style text-entry boxes in the UI.
- You should use Next.js as it works best with Vercel. 
- This frontend will ultimately be deployed on Vercel, but it should be possible to test locally. 
- Always provide users with a way to run the created UI once you have created it.

### Design & Theming

#### Color Scheme
- **Primary**: #4F46E5 (indigo-600) - Main actions, buttons, links
- **Secondary**: #10B981 (emerald-500) - Success states, confirmations
- **Accent**: #F59E0B (amber-500) - Highlights, warnings, important elements
- **Background**: #F8FAFC (slate-50) - Main background
- **Surface**: #FFFFFF (white) - Cards, panels, elevated elements
- **Text Primary**: #1E293B (slate-800) - Main text content
- **Text Secondary**: #64748B (slate-500) - Subtle text, labels
- **Border**: #E2E8F0 (slate-200) - Subtle borders and dividers

#### Design Principles
- **Modern & Clean**: Minimalist design with plenty of whitespace
- **Consistent Spacing**: Use consistent padding and margins (8px, 16px, 24px, 32px)
- **Smooth Transitions**: Subtle animations for hover states and interactions
- **Mobile-First**: Responsive design that works on all screen sizes
- **Accessibility**: High contrast ratios, clear focus states, readable typography

#### Typography
- **Primary Font**: System fonts (Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif)
- **Code Font**: Monospace for code blocks and technical content
- **Font Sizes**: 14px base, 16px for body text, 18px+ for headings

#### Component Guidelines
- **Buttons**: Rounded corners (6px), hover effects, clear hierarchy
- **Cards**: Subtle shadows, rounded corners (8px), clean borders
- **Forms**: Clear labels, helpful error messages, logical tab order
- **Chat Interface**: Clear message bubbles, distinct user/assistant styling